Ooooh today felt excellent, dear Adriene. I've been a night owl tonight, and just finished the practice at 1 am but it flew by!!! Doing this practice after my housemates and I had an impromptu, makeshift graduation party for ourselves :) It felt sooo good to just unwind and let my body recharge and refresh. As we did the wide legged, reflection staring fold, my body moved so slowly, almost building heat with just that bend! You were starting to move on, but I made the choice to continue the journey down, letting my head get closer and closer to the earth. No contact was made (yet) but it still felt different, and as I observed my body in that moment, it was something new. Something that felt right to explore. Thank you so much! See you all tomorrow <3

I can tell that I need a slower practice. Not easier, just slower. I like to explore each position some more, I just need more time to settle. So my feedback so far would be to change more back and forth between the more core-oriented practices, which can be faster too, and the ones that are more about exploring. In other words, it can be hard to properly work on breath, alignment and range of motion in each shape, if the pace is too high. I appreciate your teaching, and will definitely finish the 30 days still, but I know which direction I want to head in afterwards.

Man. I didn't think I'd comment throughout this journey. Getting on the mat hasn't been entirely easy or difficult for me. I've stuck with it, but wasn't feeling any sort of breakthrough or a shift in energy. But today was different. 

I never usually practice at home, and I've noticed how easily distracted I am at home with my To Do list not far away and dishes that need to be washed around me. I've had difficulty focusing on the practice. Today, however, I stopped at one cup of coffee, went to work and came home and cleaned up my apartment, took a long and contemplative bath then lit some candles and flowed through this. This was the first day where I just closed my eyes and trusted myself and Adriene to guide my body. Today was the first day I heard the ending music and didn't rush to my next thing. I just laid down and felt the energy in my body. The word "grace" fell through me. The feeling did too. Thank you Adriene. I didn't think I'd feel this today, or any time soon. I am so grateful towards this community. Towards myself. And towards the practice of moving and listening to your body that is yoga. <3

It’s easy to get caught up in ’doing’, so it’s kind of fun to stumble or fall because it’s an opportunity for a nice, kind chuckle. Something I’ve worked to do is to say silly things or make cute noises when accidents happen, so when I fall or get unexpectedly hurt there’s no anger to bring in, instead I get to laugh and it also usually makes other people laugh too. 
I stumbled today but it gave me a chance to laugh, which makes me smile, and reminds me to not be so serious. The poses only work when you’re relaxed, not serious or tense.

Also, I hope it’s ok to ask, I’m not sure if there’s a way to change it so late but the difference in volume between the orchestra music and your voice is very big. I have hearing problems so I turn my tv loud to hear you, but the loudness of the orchestra is startling and causes me to rush out of the final quiet moment to get the remote to turn it down. Is it possible to lower it? No big if not!

This entire journey thus far has been about grace for me. I'm learning to dedicate myself to the practice of yoga, but secondary to that is learning to give myself grace in everything and when I need it. I'm not able to do every posture because of tightness in my shoulders or not having worked out consistently in over a year. At first I was really hard on myself for that, but slowly I have become okay with that. And through giving myself grace, I've been able to accept my body in a way that I haven't done in a long time. I'm not harsh on my physical ability or the way that I look, and that is everything to me.

On the mat, we make space for the good stuff…. but is life always good or graceful?
Of course not.
The tools of yoga provide us the tools to navigate all of it.
Ride the wave of your breath and find a softness as we continue to create a full body experience, mindfully.
Try to stay out of your head today and close to the wisdom of your heart.
Also, remember to have fun with it.
